вЂ‹LeetCode 283: Move Zeroes
вЂ‹Goal: Move all zeros in an array to the end while maintaining the relative order of the non-zero elements. This must be done in-place.
вЂ‹Approach: Two-Pointer (Optimal)
вЂ‹We use two pointers, i and j.
вЂ‹i (The Explorer): Iterates through the entire array to find non-zero elements.
вЂ‹j (The Anchor): Keeps track of the position where the next non-zero element should be placed.
вЂ‹Whenever we find a non-zero element at nums[i], we swap it with the element at nums[j] and increment j. This effectively "pushes" the zeros to the right and "pulls" the numbers to the left.
вЂ‹Efficiency
вЂ‹Time Complexity: O(n), where n is the number of elements. We traverse the array exactly once.
вЂ‹Space Complexity: O(1), as we do not use any extra data structures; we modify the input array in place.
